path parameter vs query parameter
Path parameters are often used in RESTful APIs to identify a specific resource, such as a user or a produc
Query parameters, on the other hand, are part of the URL query string and are typically used to filter or modify the response data.

This request adds a search term as a query parameter q=postman ("q" refers to "query" here) to the GET /search path on Google's server.
we can change a search directly from the URL by changing the value for the query parameter
